<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Prolong" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Prolong,</orth> 1) to lengthen, to draw out in time: <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.52" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 1, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.3.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 3, 96</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 29</bibl>.<lb />2) to defer, to put off: <cit><quote>this wedding-day perhaps is but --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.256" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 256</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I am not so well provided as else I would be, were the day --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.4.47" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 4, 47</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>